The Fiery Triathlon starts this Thursday night (March 8) at 8:00 PM
MST and culminates Sunday night (march 11) at 6:00 PM MST.  It will
consist of three speed leveling challenges.  Participants will compete
using new characters to attempt to be named Fiery's fastest!

All participants will receive rewards and winners will receive their
choice from a set of predetermined quest equipment, permanent stat
increases, race change on one of their characters.

There will be three separate competitions, which will occur in order.
The first competition will be 70 Hours long, beginning March 8 and
finishing March 11.  The next two competitions will be much shorter
and both occur the night of March 11, starting at 6PM MST.

As mentioned above, all participants will receive rewards and winners
of each competition will receive prizes.  Points will also be awarded
to 1st, 2nd, and 3rd places in each competition, and players with the
highest point totals at the end of the night will receive another prize!

The specific competitions will occur as follows (no real relation
between the names and the actual challenges):

1) The Swimming Challenge (regular leveling)
This is an ordinary character leveling contest.  Players must create
new characters on or after March 8 at 8 PM MST, and may not group   
with characters created before the beginning of the contest.  At the end
of the 70 hours, the character with the highest level will win.  Players
need to create their characters on the night of March 8, and they
must register their characters to be eligible to win.

2) The Running Challenge (newbie leveling)
Players must create new characters.  A 1-level grouping restriction
will be in effect.  The first player to level 10 wins the match.
Small prizes will also be awarded for the first players to reach level 2
and level 5.

3) The Biking Challenge (endgame leveling)
Players must create new characters or reuse characters from the
newbie challenge
participants will be set to level 98 and may choose
a subclass.  Players may use two characters in tandem. The winner will   be the 
first player to reach ** on all characters they are playing.  Players will  receive a 
predetermined set of equipment, including weapons, armor, and pre-scribed spellbooks.

Further rules may be posted during the competitions.  Violations of
the posted rules as stated will result in immediate disqualification
from all three challenges.  Violations of the spirit of the rules will
be dealt with on a case-by-case basis by Lokari.

All prizes will be awarded at the end of the competition on or after March 11.
Posted information is subject to change at the gods' discretion. If you have 
any ideas, questions, or problems with the times, don't hesitate to post!~
