subject: &2 Help File Addition
message:
   Yuhen and i would like to invite the players to contribute ideas for a new
help file page that will help newbies pick useful character pairs/sets.  If
you would like to contribute please email your thoughts to ramah(at)fierymud.
Org .  Feel free to input anything about good sets you wish you had known when
you were new.  Be sure to include your ideas for great, good, and bad sets as
well as the character name you wish to be know as in the help file.

&bCHARACTER SETS

   Each class or subclass has its own strengths and weaknesses.  This page has
been created to help players early on to make effective character sets.  
These are some of the sets players have found to be worthwhile, followed by
some less-inspiring match-ups, along with some explanations.

   3 star sets favorites of many players : sets that give you a well rounded
team as well as a full gaming experience.
   * necro and thief (having a thief to see your zombies inventory is super
helpful)
   * paladin and sorcerer (paladin is a great tank and can keep himself alive
and the sorcerer can crank out damage safe from harm)

   2 star sets boring but effective sets : these are still good sets but you
might limit your gameplay experience because of your set
   * druid and sorcerer (funny but no one will take you seriously)

   1 star sets unimpressive sets : it is important to state that there are no
bad groups but.  You might want to avoid.  Any set that is the same class, any
set that has conflicting alignments.
   * paladin/anti and priest/dia (so much overlap in character strengths and
weaknesses that it leaves a lot to be desired)
   * Solo, doesnt matter what class.  (most classes can get by, but its
painfully slow and eventually not as fun or capable as teamwork)

A special thanks to the players namely (&2your name here&0) for contributing
to the helpfile of fierymud~
~~
