level: 105
poster: Chinok
time: 1639489782
subject: December 14 Equipment update info
message:
Big changes have come to Fiery's equipment!
Second, armor and weapon restrictions have been changed across the game!
- We have made an attempt to divide armor and weapons into several 
  conceptual categories:
1. All objects are either natural (including purely magical) or forged
2. Armors are heavy (forged metals, rock/stone), 
   medium (wood, dragonscale, bone, chainmail, scalemail, ringmail), 
   light (leather, fabric, plant, fur, hair, feather, paper, magic/
   elemental), or shields.
3. Weapon types are: dagger, shortsword (includes most pickaxes), 
   and 1 or 2 handed versions of sword, spear, axe (includes most scythes
   and sickles), mace/hammer, club, and staff.
- Many accessories have had their class restrictions removed, 
  but alignment restrictions tightened.
- Daggers, 1h clubs, and 1h staves are now usable by any class, although
  many unique or esoteric weapons remain exclusive to particular skill lines,
  religions, or mystical practices.
- These categories are NOT hard-coded.  There may be errors or oversights, 
  but there's also conceptual or practical wiggle room.  
 
- Let us know what you think!
- After decades of being free to wear anything they want, Monks are now 
  subject to gear restrictions just like everyone else. They are now 
  restricted from most armors of chainmail weight and heavier, nor can
  they use shields of any kind anymore.  Furthermore, they are no longer
  capable of wielding most weapons even if they want to for some reason.
  This may result in a complete overhaul of a Monk's gear.
- Rogues, Thieves, and Assassins may now use most single-handed swords and
  shields.  Rogues and Thieves are limited to lighter armor, but 
  Assassins can wear full chain.
- Mercenaries cannot wear most heavy forged armors anymore, but can use any 
  type of weapon.
- Sorcerers, Pyromancers, and Cryomancers should now find knowing what they 
  can and cannot wear a little more intuitive.  They can only use armor made
  from very light or highly magical materials; they can use fur, but not 
  leather.  Except in a few rare instances, they cannot use 
  shields anymore either.
- Necromancers have nearly identical restrictions to Sorcerers now.  For 
  years, much of the earliest gear lacked the Necromancer restriction 
  because it was developed before the class was implemented.  We were
  sure to correct most of those oversights on this pass.
- Clerics, Priests, and Diabolists may now use most armors and shields.
  Although they can now use most daggers, they do not have the piercing 
  weapon proficiency.  They still cannot use swords, axes, or spears.
- Druids now have the most conceptual limitations on their equipment.  
  They can now use nearly anything made of a natural or purely magical 
  substance, provided it doesn't interfere with their alignment.  Any 
  one-handed weapon that may be useful in gardening, harvesting, or 
  hunting can also now be used.  Larger weapons and swords are still 
  off-limits to them.
- Rangers have been caught in paradigm shifts for years.  We're currently 
  treating them as moderately-armored hunters with all the weapon 
  prowess of Warriors.
Future projects:
- By and large items have NOT been rebalanced yet.  This is the next project 
  we'll be working on in the background.
- Weapon damage messages may also be inconsistent (eg some shortswords are 
  pierce, some are slash).  We hope to align that soon, since that does play
  a significant role for Rogue-types, particularly Assassins.
- We're hoping to make gearing more consistent across the leveling 
  experience by adjusting items to reflect the level of the zones they
  come from.  We'll be adjusting both item levels and item strength to 
  accomplish that."~
~~
