poster: Daedela
time: 1645164937
subject: Recent XP scale changes
message:
Hope you all read the news!&_
If you did, you know we updated the XP scales for several classes.
Previously, Pyros, Cryos, Paladins, and Antis all needed the standard 100% experience.
Paladins and Antis now need 115%, equivalent to Rangers, and Pyros and Cryos need 120%, the same as base Sorcerer.
We increased these numbers because these classes previously needed /less/ XP to level than their base classes, 
despite having equivalent or better abilities.&_
Monks needed 150% because of all their abilities and the lack of gear restriction.
Having added that restriction though, we have reduced their XP scale to 130%.
Monks immediately saw their levels go up as their current XP totals were matched to the new level values.&_
A small problem we did not foresee however was what would happen to all the ** characters of classes who we adjusted upward.&_
Although we changed their XP scales, unlike with Monks,
all these characters stayed at their current XP total of 100% instead of the new maximums AND also their current level.
If/when they die, their level is still 99, so they lose 25% of the new expected amount from the 115% or 120% scale,
rather than 25% of the previous 100% scale.
Also as it turns out, the amount of experience you need to get from 99 to ** for all classes is /astronomical/.
It's roughly equivalent to the experience needed to get from halfway through level 96 to 99.
So this new much larger amount is subtracted from the existing much lower total,
then the game does the normal thing to check what level the new XP total should be and sets the character to that.
This results in level 99 players losing 4-5 levels at their first death,
which is exactly what would happen to some Monks after they subclassed previously.&_
It also means it is going to take some time before the experience meter starts increasing again -
being at less experience than the level minimum isn't something we ever planned for it to indicate!&_
I apologize for the bump in the roll out on this.
Some of you are upset.  I fully empathize with your dissatisfaction.
But I promise you, soon you won't even notice the difference!&_
Daedela~
~~
