subject: More Gear Changes Ahead
message:
As you may have noticed, Fiery is going through some revamping behind the scenes.
I wanted to give you a heads up about one that is going to impact all of you:
Equipment stat changes!
 
This overhaul is long overdue.
With the successful implementation of the !monk bit, we're finally in a place to 
make some minor to moderate changes in the stats of most of the gear.
 
Our goal with this is /not/ to nerf all the existing equipment.
Our goal /is/ to make more equipment more competitive.
 
I hope to accomplish four things:
1. Create a more steady progression from level to level with gear growth
2. Make the hierarchy of what is better than what more intuitive - 
(steel should generally offer greater protection than mundane leather, for example)
3. Make gear more appropriate to the level of the zone it comes from - 
(no more level 50 1d8 longswords)
4. Reduce redundancy of item names and stats and make sure items have substantial
differences,
both in name and function.
 
Some items in the mid levels will see their effectiveness reduced a point or two.
Many weapons will see a small to significant increase in their damage.
End game gear will be largely unaffected, save a few items that still need more of
a kick to be rewarding for the effort it takes to get them.
Some items currently best in the game for some classes will see their levels
dramatically increased so you aren't getting the best gear at level 30.
This should hopefully be commensurate with the practical challenge it to get them. 
 
Any gear currently in existence will NOT be affected.
If you have it, it's yours and it can't be changed unless you get it altered at the
repair shop or by a god.
 
I can't give an exact timeline other than "soon", but know the planning is well underway
and I hope to start rolling this out in the low-level zones soon.
 
If you have questions or comments, please feel free to chat with me in game or email me
at daedela@@fierymud.org.
 
Daedela~
~~
