subject: Phase armor gem overhaul notes
message:
The phase armor gem system has long been counter-intuitive and seemingly
random.  Today we release an overhaul of the &7&bnaming system&0 for the gems,
hoping it will make knowing which gems to keep a lot easier.  The &7&bcode&0 for
the quests &2&bhas not changed.&0  It will still function exactly the same.
Our questing system does &7&bNOT&0 use item names to function.
 
The new system uses an even progression of adjectives that should be more
intuitive to follow.
Phase 1 Gems
 - dust -> crushed -> shard
 
Phase 2 gems
 - uncut -> flawed -> <no adjective*>
*for ease of gathering and sorting, these gems now all have the keyword
"plain", but that word will not be included in the gem's visual description.
 
Phase 3 gems
 - perfect -> radiant -> enchanted
 
All classes will consistently use &7&bthe same gem variety&0 across their
class-specific quests.  For example, all clerics (and priests) will use only
amethysts, garnets, and rubies all quests.  Diabolists will use amethyst,
garnet, and ruby for Phase 1, but then carnelian, beryl, and ruby for
Phases 2 and 3.  No other class will use amethyst, garnet, carnelian, or beryl.
 
One important exception: &7&ball body gems will be a ruby, sapphire, diamond,
or emerald.&0  These four varieties of gems will &7&bONLY&0 be used for the body
armor quests.  For example, a perfect, radiant, and enchanted ruby are three
different Phase 3 body gems.  They are not used for any other gear type and
have no difference in value or importance.
 
To make this work, there are now &7&b26 varieties&0 of gems, 14 of which will
&7&bnot appear&0 in Phase 1. 
 
On a technical note, we have been able to do this without changing any of the
back-end code used to run the quests.  Therefore, the quest masters will still
accept gems with the &7&bold names&0 for their respective rewards.
 
There is one exception, as part of the previous quest triggers were incorrectly
written.  The &6&bsorcerer phase 2 head gem&0 should have been
&3&ba handful of amber&0, not &3&ban enchanted amethyst&0.  That has been
corrected in the code, so going forward if any handfuls of amber are floating
around, the quest master will accept them in place of the new gem but will not
accept an enchanted amethyst.
 
We are working to correct every gem currently held by every player.  As that
may take some time, you are welcome to visit Tr'ven in Mielikki and manually
exchange your gems.  You may also exchange them at the Anduin branch of the
Soltan Gem Exchange!  I have also posted the converted names to the player
board.
 
Again I want to stress, with the exception of the sorcerer phase 2 head gem
correction, this change is &7&bpurely visual&0 to increase comprehensibility.
 
If there are any questions, please reach out to me directly!
 
All the best,
Daedela~
~~
level: 104
poster: Daedela
time: 1668598931
subject: Bless/Hex changes
message:
Bless, Earth Blessing, and Dark Presence have had their core functionality
changed.  They will all still continue to modify save vs spell as they always
have, and duration will be determined by skill.
 
At the highest levels, all three spells will now function like Dark Presence 
always has and provide a small bonus to damage.
 
The greatest change is in how these spells alter hitroll.  Previously only
these spells modified hitroll, not items which provided a Bless or Hex effect.
Now, any player under the effect of a Bless or Hex, whether from one of the 
above spells OR from an item with the effect on it, will see a change to their
hitroll.  The amount will depend on their level, rather than the character or 
object which cast the effect.
 
Additionally, the magnitude of the bonus will differ depending on character
alignment and the alignment of the creature being attacked.  Characters will
see a large increase when attacking targets of the opposite alignment, and a
moderate increase against neutral targets.  However, characters will notice a 
moderate DECREASE in their hitroll when attacking targets of the same 
alignment.  Neutral characters will see only a moderate increase against good 
OR evil targets, but suffer no penalty against neutral ones.~
~~
